# If you prefer the allow list template instead of the deny list, see community template:
# https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/community/Golang/Go.AllowList.gitignore
#
# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Code coverage profiles and other test artifacts
*.out
coverage.*
*.coverprofile
profile.cov

# Compiled binary output (Makefile `build` target writes bin/holos-paas).
/bin/

# Go dependency directory.  Anchored to the repo root: Go vendoring only
# creates vendor/ at the module root, and component-level vendor/ trees under
# holos/components/ are committed Helm chart caches that must stay visible
# (see holos/docs/component-guidelines.md).
/vendor/

# Go workspace file
go.work
go.work.sum

# env file
.env

# Editor/IDE
.idea/
.vscode/
.claude/

# In-progress download directories created by read-thru-cache scripts.  The
# EXIT trap removes them, but a SIGKILL bypasses traps and could strand one
# inside the component tree.
**/manifests/.tmp.*

# Temporary render/package working directories created by scripts/publish and
# scripts/apply-my-project under the holos module root (holos render platform
# writes relative to that root).  The EXIT trap removes them, but a SIGKILL
# bypasses traps and could strand one.
holos/.publish.*
holos/.apply-my-project.*

# Holos files
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
ehthumbs.db
Thumbs.db
node_modules/
tmp/
